    <text corresp="#c5681">
        <body>
            <div corresp="#c5681f1">
                <head>TIENTSIN: China</head>
                <p>HISTORY (established, opened, closed, etc.)</p>
                <p>CG est. - CG closed 12/7/41 - CG est. 10/7/45, open 12/17/45<lb/>Closed to Public
                    2/25/50. Closed officially 4/14/50.</p>
                <p>REMARKS:</p>
                <p>PB MEMO NOS.</p>
                <p>DEPT.CONTACTS</p>
                <table>
                    <row role="label">
                        <cell>DATE</cell>
                        <cell>ACTION, COMMUNICATIONS, REMARKS, ETC.</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell>12/7/41 US</cell>
                        <cell>CG closed on declaration of war on US by Japan. Non-conf.records &amp;
                            archives<lb/>ordered stored locally. Conf. codes burned, contents of
                            locked cash box<lb/>destroyed.</cell>
                    </row>
                </table>
            </div>
            <div corresp="#c5681f2">
                <head>Tientsin</head>
                <table>
                    <row role="label">
                        <cell>10/7/45</cell>
                        <cell>CG est. Opened to public on 12/17/45. Ref. desp. 11/18/45 from
                            Tientsin (125.937/11.1845) giving detailed info re services actually
                            performed prior to formal opening to public --Performing most services,
                            but have not formally taken over records from Swiss.</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell>7/23/49</cell>
                        <cell>Tgm 538 from Tientsin quotes let. from Military Control Committee
                            ordering USIS activities terminated. USIS closed date of tgm.</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell>1/24/50</cell>
                        <cell>DA Mailing Notice No. 11 - Tientsin instructed on January 14, 1950 to
                            close as soon as transportation could be arranged. Brit. to handle
                            American interests. Mail should be sent in accordance with Dept. Regs.,
                            Dept. Announcement No. 221 and DA Mailing Notice No. 1.</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell>2/17/50</cell>
                        <cell>Tel. to Tientsin #124 of this date re auth. ship 10 cases records
                            direct to DEPT. Classified portion via pouch, unclassified portion via
                            U.S. Despatch Agent and via safe means.</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell>2/18/50</cell>
                        <cell>Tel. 186 from Tientsin of this date re closing Congen 2/25/50.
                            Cryptographic material retained until 3/10/50 then burned. Alien staff
                            terminated 2/25/50. More valuable items office furniture and equipment
                            and certain files moved to office of British Congen. Brit. not wish
                            license US real properties. Congen has two leased quarters FA-33 and
                            office quarters FA-34</cell>
                    </row>
                </table>
            </div>
        </body>
